[Thanks to Tulio de Oliveira's tweet "Shedding light on the start of the COVID-19 pandemic in Cape Town & SA! European lineages introduced and supermarket outbreaks fuelled the 1st cluster of infections. Great collaboration" (https://mobile.twitter.com/Tuliodna).

This is a very nice study elucidating the introduction of virus into South Africa, which started the outbreak. It is interesting that a large outbreak occurred in a supermarket, as demonstrated by those strains making up a large monophyletic cluster. Supermarkets were "among the few essential services allowed to continue operating during lockdown level 5 in South Africa." The extent of transmission could have been much worse had most institutions, commercial and other, not locked down. - Mod.LK]

