[B] India
Date: Fri 9 Apr 2021 03:50 IST
Source: The Times of India (TOI), Times News Network (TNN) [edited]
https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/total-caseload-tops-13-million-last-1-million-in-record-11-days/articleshow/81978216.cms


Even as fresh COVID-19 infections hit another single-day peak of over 1.3 lakh [130 000] on [Thu 8 Apr 2021], the country's total caseload crossed 13 million (1.3 crore), with the last 1 million cases coming in just 11 days.

The time taken for the count to rise from 12 million to 13 million equaled the record for the fastest 1 million increase in cases, when the count rose from 4 million to 5 million in 11 days during the peak of the 1st wave in September [2020].

India has so far reported 13 057 812 cases of the coronavirus, the 3rd highest total in the world after the US (31.6 million) and Brazil (13.2 million).

India has been logging the highest daily cases of the virus over the past few days.

On [Thu 8 Apr 2021], the country reported 131 918 new cases, beating the previous highest of 1.26 lakh [126 000] recorded the previous day [Wed 7 Apr 2021]. This was the 4th fresh peak in daily cases since the count topped the 1 lakh [100 000] mark on [Sun 4 Apr 2021] amid a surge in the pandemic numbers across the country.

Thursday's [8 Apr 2021] COVID death toll rose to 802, which was the 1st time in 173 days since [17 Oct] last year [2020] that the daily casualty count had exceeded 800.

Maharashtra alone recorded 376 deaths in the last 24 hours, followed by Chhattisgarh, where as many as 94 fatalities were reported. Punjab recorded 56 deaths, Uttar Pradesh, 39; Karnataka, 36; Gujarat, 35; Madhya Pradesh, 27; and Delhi, 24.

As many as 5 states logged their biggest ever single-day surge in COVID cases, evidence that the pandemic's 2nd wave was now raging across most of the country.

The 5 states were Chhattisgarh, where 10 652 fresh cases were detected, marginally higher than Wednesday's [7 Apr 2021] all-time high of 10 310.

Fresh cases in Uttar Pradesh touched a new peak of 8490 for the 1st time since the 1st wave. Similarly, Rajasthan reported a new high of 3526, while Gujarat cases topped 4000 for the 1st time at 4021. Madhya Pradesh's tally climbed yet again to 4324.

Another 12 states reported their daily surge of cases in 2021, including Delhi (7437 cases, highest since [19 Nov 2020]), Tamil Nadu (4276, the highest since [17 Oct 2020] ), Haryana (2872, [20 Nov 2020]), Bengal (2783, [10 Dec 2020]), Andhra Pradesh (2558, [5 Nov 2020]), Telangana (2055, [7 Oct 2020]), Bihar (1911, [4 Sep 2020]), and Jharkhand (1882, the highest since [9 Sep 2020]).

Infections have been rising in Kerala as well. The state logged 4353 new cases on [Thu 8 Apr 2021], the most since [20 Feb 2021].

[Byline: Amit Bhattacharya]

