[C] Nepal
Date: Wed 7 Apr 2021 03:57 p.m. NPT
Source: The Himalayan Times [abridged, edited]
https://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/nepal-records-298-new-cases-of-covid-19-in-24-hours-nationwide-tally-hits-278768


Nepal on [Wed 7 Apr 2021] reported 298 new cases of coronavirus infection from across the country. With this, the nationwide infection count has advanced to 278 768.

Of the total cases recorded today [7 Apr 2021], Kathmandu district observed 132 new infections. Kathmandu holds the highest number of new cases recorded today [7 Apr 2021].

Likewise, 74 people who were earlier infected with the virus are reported to have recovered in the past 24 hours as per the latest data provided by health ministry. As of today [7 Apr 2021], 273 529 individuals have recovered from the novel coronavirus infection. The recovery rate, as such, is 98.1%.

Nepal's active COVID-19 case count currently stands at 2201.

The nationwide death toll currently stands at 3038 with 2 COVID-related fatalities reported today [7 Apr 2021].

According to the health ministry, 4100 PCR tests were conducted in the last 24 hours. With this, a total of 2 298 167 PCR tests have been carried out in Nepal to date [7 Apr 2021].

Similarly, of the total 1040 antigen tests carried out at various entry points into the country, 41 antigen positive cases were detected.

Currently, there are 65 individuals in various quarantine facilities across Nepal.

On [Tue 6 Apr 2021], Nepal's coronavirus case count reached 278 470 with 260 newly confirmed cases.

