Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Data by country, area, or territory for 9 Apr 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20Apr9_1618077900.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 33.7% of daily case numbers and 50.6% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 57.51 million cases. Brazil reported over 92 000 cases over the last 24 hours followed by the USA with 74 849 cases and Argentina with 22 039 cases; 12 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (Colombia, Peru, Chile, Canada, Mexico, Uruguay, Paraguay, Ecuador, Guatemala, Venezuela, Dominican Republic, and Bolivia). Cuba and Honduras reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 35.1% of daily case numbers and 34.3% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours; total cumulative cases reported exceed 47.04 million and cumulative deaths crossed the 1 million mark in last 24 hours. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium (2 cases), Switzerland (7 cases), and Kazakhstan, among others. Turkey reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Poland, Germany, France, Ukraine, and Italy, reporting more than 10 000 new cases in the past 24 hours. Another 21 countries reported more than 1000 cases, and an additional 9 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 8.1% of daily case numbers and 5.3% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 7.95 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (22 586) over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, Pakistan, Jordan, Lebanon, Palestinian Authority, UAE, Tunisia, Kuwait, Oman, and Bahrain. Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Libya, Egypt, and Moroocco reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 1.0% of daily case numbers and 1.1 % of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.15 million cases. Ethiopia (2121) reported the highest number of cases over last 24 hours followed by Kenya (1698) and South Africa (1366). Cameroon, Botswana, and Guinea, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 2.1% of daily case numbers and 0.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 2.03 million cases. Philippines reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 9000 cases), followed by Japan, Malaysia, South Korea, and Mongolia.

- The South East Asia region reported 19.9% of the daily newly reported cases and 7.9% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 15.85 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 131 000 cases, followed by Bangladesh (6854), Indonesia (5504), Thailand, Sri Lanka, and Nepal.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 9 Apr 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

